==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# {{obsolete}}: A waiting for. [[Ambush]]; [[heed]]; [[watch]]; [[watching]].

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|await||}}

[[Transitive]]:
# (''formal'') To [[wait]] for.
#:''I '''await''' your reply to my letter.''
# To wait on, [[serve]], or [[attend]] (to).
# To [[expect]].
# To be in store for; to be ready or in waiting for
#:''A glorious reward '''awaits''' the good.''

[[Intransitive]]:
# To watch.
# To wait (on or upon).
# To wait; to stay in waiting.

====Usage notes====
*As '''await''' means ''to wait for'', it is not followed by "for".  ''I am awaiting for your reply'' is therefore incorrect.

